{"title_page": "Mike Reilly (1980s linebacker)", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Mike Reilly\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| number              = 57\n| position            = [[Linebacker]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1959|2|14}}\n| birth_place         = [[Miami, Florida]]\n| death_date          =\n| death_place         =\n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 4\n| weight_lbs          = 217\n| high_school         = [[Christopher Columbus High School (Miami-Dade County)|Christopher Columbus]]<br>Miami, Florida\n| college             = [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]]\n| draftyear           = 1982\n| draftround          = 8\n| draftpick           = 207\n| pastteams           =\n* [[Los Angeles Rams]] ({{NFL Year|1982}})\n| highlights          =\n}}\n'''Michael Dennis Reilly''' (born February 14, 1959)<ref name=pfr>{{cite web|title=Mike Reilly|work=Pro Football Reference|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/R/ReilMi21.htm|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref> is an American former professional [[American football|football]] player who was a [[linebacker]] with the [[Los Angeles Rams]] in the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] with the [[Oklahoma Sooners]], and was drafted by the Rams in the eighth round of the [[1982 NFL Draft]].<ref name=pfr/><ref name=hoffer_01121988>{{cite news|last=Hoffer|first=Richard|title=The New, Sober Life of Reilly : Ex-Ram, an Alcoholic, Lives With a Death|date=January 12, 1988|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1988-01-12-sp-35206-story.html|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref> During training camp as a Rams rookie in 1982, Reilly was involved in a car accident that killed a 17-year old boy. He served a one-year jail sentence for [[drunken driving]] and felony [[vehicular manslaughter]].<ref name=hoffer_01121988/><ref>{{cite news|title=Los Angeles Rams linebacker and jail inmate Mike Reilly...|date=August 2, 1983|publisher=UPI|url=https://www.upi.com/Archives/1983/08/02/Los-Angeles-Rams-linebacker-and-jail-inmate-Mike-Reilly/3758428644800/|accessdate=August 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{football stats |pfr=R/ReilMi21}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reilly, Mike}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football linebackers]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Rams players]]\n[[Category:Oklahoma Sooners football players]]\n\n{{linebacker-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Mike Reilly\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| number              = 57\n| position            = [[Linebacker]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1959|2|14}}\n| birth_place         = [[Miami, Florida]]\n| death_date          =\n| death_place         =\n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 4\n| weight_lbs          = 217\n| high_school         = [[Christopher Columbus High School (Miami-Dade County)|Christopher Columbus]]<br>Miami, Florida\n| college             = [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]]\n| draftyear           = 1982\n| draftround          = 8\n| draftpick           = 207\n| pastteams           =\n* [[Los Angeles Rams]] ({{NFL Year|1982}})\n| highlights          =\n}}\n'''Michael Dennis Reilly''' (born February 14, 1959)<ref name=pfr>{{cite web|title=Mike Reilly|work=Pro Football Reference|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/R/ReilMi21.htm|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref> is an American former professional [[American football|football]] player who was a [[linebacker]] with the [[Los Angeles Rams]] in the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] with the [[Oklahoma Sooners]], and w